    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka health sector union leader lands new job under president",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka trade union leader Saman Rathnapriya, who is affiliated with the United National Party (UNP), has been appointed Director General of Trade Unions by President Ranil Wickremesinghe.",
        "A press release from the President\u2019s Media Division confirmed the appointment on Tuesday August 02.",
        "Rathnapriya, who once represented the UNP in parliament, was President of the Government Nursing Officers\u2019 Association. As a trade union leader, he was prominently active during the presidency of Gotabaya Rajapaksa throughout the COVID-19 public health emergency. (Colombo/Aug02/2022)"
      ],
